A linear regression model that predicts the proposed percentage share for the opponent based on a normalized difference between opponent and participant tokens. The intercept (a) sets the baseline (fair split) and the slope (b) adjusts proposals based on fairness considerations, with a normally distributed noise (epsilon) governed by sigma.
</SUMMARY>

